As the political trajectory ahead of the 2023 general election continues to take shape, some former presidential candidates in the 2019 elections, have formed a new political association named the National Interest Forum (NIF). NIF which is under the chairmanship of Shitu Mohammed, an ex-presidential candidate on the platform of All Progressives Democratic Alliance (APDA), held their inaugural meeting last Thursday at the Transcorp Hilton Abuja, with an agenda to galvanize ideas towards the attainment of national unity. Besides Mohammed, Mohammed Danjuma, a former presidential candidate under the platform of Movement for the Restoration and Defence of Democracy (MRDD) is also a key member of the association. Speaking on the intent of the group, Mohammed emphasised: “National interest should be above personal interest. It is time we join hands together to move the country forward. National interest must drive our common aspirations.” Some other politicians who attended the meeting include Sen. Abdullahi Gumel, Hon Albert Abiodun Adeogun, a two-time House of Representatives member, Hon Edozien Madu and Hajia Umma Getso among others. They unanimously agreed national interest should and must supersede personal gains. They also underscored the need for Nigerians to unite as an indivisible entity. 